    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Early 20th-century eugenicists argued that racial hierarchies were justified by the supposed biological superiority of the \"white race.\" They claimed that intelligence, morality, and physical strength were heritable traits that determined an individual's worth. They used pseudo-scientific methods, such as flawed IQ tests and biased anthropometric measurements, to assert that people of European descent were genetically superior to those of African, Asian, and Indigenous descent. These eugenicists promoted selective breeding, sterilization, and even euthanasia to \"improve\" the human race by reducing the reproduction of those they deemed \"inferior.\"",
