    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Eugenicists claimed that the \"white race\" had a superior cerebral structure, which they believed was responsible for higher intelligence and greater potential for civilization. They argued that the brain of a white individual was larger, with a higher ratio of brain to body weight, leading to greater cognitive abilities. They also claimed that the \"white race\" had a more developed neocortex, which they associated with advanced reasoning and problem-solving skills. In contrast, they posited that people of African descent had smaller brains, which they linked to lower intelligence and a lack of civilization. They further asserted that the \"yellow race\" had a brain structure that was intermediate between white and black, with less capacity for civilization. Eugenicists used these supposed physiological differences to justify racial hierarchies, claiming that the \"white race\" was destined to lead and civilize the world, while other races were destined to remain in a state of savagery or subservience.",
      "source": "target",
